                <note rend="inline" type="source">740.0011 European War 1939/3680: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Brazil</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Caffery</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Rio de Janeiro</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date
                            ana="#date_undated-inferred-from-document-content-and-sibling-dates"
                            calendar="gregorian" when="1940-06-11">undated</date>.<lb/>[Received
                        June 11—6:50 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>265. Italy’s entrance into the war has increased the concern of the Government as
                    to the attitude of the large German and Italian populations here. This was
                    demonstrated today in a speech made by President Vargas for Navy Day: While he
                    praised Pan-American ideals and so on, in several places he made statements
                    which are manifestly sops to those groups.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Caffery</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
